# Frontend Development Rules

**CRITICAL:**
- Frontend is NOT pre-configured - run `@init-frontend` first (creates `/frontend` with Vite + React + TypeScript)
- Only modify files in `/frontend` - NEVER touch `/backend` or root config files
- Working directory: `/frontend` for all operations
- Package manager: `bun` (preferred) or `npm` (auto-detected) - use `bun` commands, fallback to `npm` equivalents

## Tech Stack
- React 19+ with TypeScript, Vite (HMR enabled)
- UI: shadcn/ui (default), Tailwind CSS (via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin)
- Config files: `vite.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, `tsconfig.app.json`, `eslint.config.js`, `.env` (gitignored)

## Project Structure
```
frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── main.tsx, App.tsx, App.css, index.css
│   ├── components/ (including ui/ for shadcn components)
│   ├── hooks/, utils/, assets/
├── vite.config.ts (includes API proxy)
└── package.json, tsconfig.json, eslint.config.js, .env
```

## Development Guidelines

**TypeScript (REQUIRED):**
- Strict type safety: explicit parameter/return types, no `any`, props interfaces required
- Use `.ts`/`.tsx` only (never `.js`/`.jsx`), prefer interfaces over types

**Components:**
- Functional components with hooks, named exports, single responsibility
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks

**UI Components Library:**
- **Default: shadcn/ui** - Copy components into your project (not installed as npm package)
- Add components: `bunx shadcn@latest add <component-name>` (or `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`) - run from `/frontend`
- Components are copied to `src/components/ui/` - customize as needed
- Uses Tailwind CSS via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin (auto-configured by `@init-frontend`)
- Tailwind CSS: `src/index.css` contains `@import "tailwindcss";` (no separate config file needed)
- Prefer shadcn components over building from scratch
- Browse components: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components
- Official setup guide: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/vite

**Running:**
- Dev: `bun run dev` (or `npm run dev`) from `/frontend` → `http://localhost:5173`
- API proxy: `/api/*` → `http://localhost:8000` (configured in `vite.config.ts`)

**API Integration:**
- Use fetch API, add TypeScript interfaces for responses
- Example pattern in `App.tsx`
- When backend changes: update interfaces, fetch calls, test in browser

## File Modification Rules

**MAY modify:** Files in `/frontend/src`, `package.json`, `.env.example`, Vite/ESLint configs
**MUST NOT modify:** `/backend` files, root `README.md`, `.cursor/` files (unless requested)

## Common Tasks

**Dependencies:** `bun add <pkg>` (or `npm install <pkg>`)
**Build:** `bun run build` → `dist/` directory
**Env vars:** Use `VITE_` prefix, access via `import.meta.env.VITE_VAR_NAME`, document in `.env.example`

## Deployment
- Static site: build → `dist/`, publish `dist/`
- Use `VITE_` prefix for client-side env vars
